title: Wall fire at famous Seattle Edgewater hotel
text:
Firefighters responded Sunday afternoon to a wall fire at the Edgewater Hotel in Seattle.
Witnesses say they saw smoke coming out of the walls.
The fire started in the wall on the first floor.
The fire was extinguished at around 1:05 p.m. No injuries were reported.
One alarm fire at the Edgewater hotel in #Seattle is out. Fire started in the wall on the 1st floor. No injuries. pic.twitter.com/lXEZRo6G16
